Brazil Stock Movers: Braskem, Gafisa, Itau Unibanco Holding Fall

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-09-12T15:03:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-12/brazil-stock-movers-braskem-gafisa-itau-unibanco-holding-fall.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 10:39 a.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index fell 1.4 percent to 54,977.11.  Braskem SA (BRKM5)  (BRKM5 BS),  Latin America ’s largest
petrochemicals producer, dropped 3.1 percent to 16.71 reais, its
lowest price in four weeks, on speculation that the global
economy will falter if Greece defaults, hindering Brazilian
exporters. Braskem owns plants in the U.S. and sells products
throughout the world. Braskem faces increased domestic
competition from international suppliers, wrote JPMorgan Chase &
Co. in a note to clients dated today. Analysts led by Caio Carvalhal rate Braskem “neutral” with a year-end price target
of 22 reais.  Itau Unibanco Holding SA (ITUB4)  (ITUB4 BS), Latin America’s
largest bank by market value, retreated 3 percent to 27.94 reais
as European banks tumbled on speculation Moody’s Investors
Service will cut ratings on French lenders.  Gafisa SA (GFSA3)  (GFSA3 BS),  Brazil ’s third-largest homebuilder by
revenue, declined 1.6 percent to 7.20 reais after it was cut to
“market perform” from “outperform” at Itau Corretora de
Valores SA.  To contact the reporter on this story:
